WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.904 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.904 --> 00:00:15.376 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:15.376 --> 00:00:28.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:31.420 align:middle line:84%
>> My name is
Vinney Todd Tolman.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:35.220 align:middle line:84%
And before my near-death
experience as a youthful,

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:39.240 align:middle line:84%
young 20-something year old,
I was out exploring life.

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:42.600 align:middle line:84%
I'd traveled the world,
done many different jobs.

00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:46.650 align:middle line:84%
And I used to do bodybuilding
or amateur bodybuilding.

00:00:46.650 --> 00:00:53.040 align:middle line:84%
And back in January 18, 2003,
it started with a new supplement

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:57.230 align:middle line:84%
that me and a really good friend
of mine had purchased online.

00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.350 align:middle line:84%
We decided, hey, we're going
to take this on a Saturday.

00:01:00.350 --> 00:01:03.120 align:middle line:84%
We're going to go up
and see a car show, do

00:01:03.120 --> 00:01:07.150 align:middle line:84%
a workout at the gym, and
just have a fun Saturday.

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:10.310 align:middle line:84%
So we get there to
hit my buddy's place.

00:01:10.310 --> 00:01:13.770 align:middle line:84%
We took this new
supplement and immediately

00:01:13.770 --> 00:01:15.840 align:middle line:90%
felt something was wrong.

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:19.410 align:middle line:84%
It felt almost as
if cold ice started

00:01:19.410 --> 00:01:21.090 align:middle line:90%
pumping through our veins.

00:01:21.090 --> 00:01:24.090 align:middle line:84%
It felt like our whole body
was starting to get cold.

00:01:24.090 --> 00:01:27.120 align:middle line:84%
And I explained to my buddy
that, hey, we should probably

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:29.410 align:middle line:84%
go get something
to eat, otherwise

00:01:29.410 --> 00:01:30.760 align:middle line:90%
we're going to be really sick.

00:01:30.760 --> 00:01:34.610 align:middle line:84%
So we went down the street a few
blocks to this fast food joint.

00:01:34.610 --> 00:01:35.860 align:middle line:90%
We go in there.

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:39.160 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as I go in, I went
straight into the bathroom.

00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:42.410 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I was going
to throw up or vomit.

00:01:42.410 --> 00:01:45.400 align:middle line:84%
My buddy, he went in, he
collapsed on the first booth

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:48.140 align:middle line:84%
he could reach, and he
started to throw up.

00:01:48.140 --> 00:01:50.150 align:middle line:84%
He started to
vomit on the table.

00:01:50.150 --> 00:01:53.030 align:middle line:84%
The manager of the
restaurant called 911.

00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:55.720 align:middle line:84%
They got him hauled
away in an ambulance

00:01:55.720 --> 00:01:58.070 align:middle line:90%
almost immediately, right away.

00:01:58.070 --> 00:02:00.800 align:middle line:84%
And he turned out
to be totally fine.

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:03.710 align:middle line:84%
They released him from the
hospital the very next day.

00:02:03.710 --> 00:02:06.460 align:middle line:84%
But meanwhile, me
inside that bathroom, I

00:02:06.460 --> 00:02:10.190 align:middle line:84%
myself start to vomit while
I'm passed out on my back.

00:02:10.190 --> 00:02:12.970 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is when you
vomit on your back like that,

00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:14.930 align:middle line:90%
you aspirate, you suffocate.

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:16.540 align:middle line:90%
And that's what happened to me.

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:21.250 align:middle line:84%
I died right there and
then on the bathroom floor.

00:02:21.250 --> 00:02:22.900 align:middle line:90%
I suffocated.

00:02:22.900 --> 00:02:26.800 align:middle line:84%
And about 45 minutes later,
the manager of the restaurant

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:29.920 align:middle line:84%
finally opened up that
bathroom after a customer kept

00:02:29.920 --> 00:02:31.870 align:middle line:90%
asking him to open it for him.

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:35.350 align:middle line:84%
He opened it and sees this
dead body on the ground.

00:02:35.350 --> 00:02:36.700 align:middle line:90%
He called 911.

00:02:36.700 --> 00:02:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And from my point of
view, I went directly

00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:44.170 align:middle line:84%
from consciousness
to feeling dizziness

00:02:44.170 --> 00:02:46.250 align:middle line:84%
as if the room is
spinning on me.

00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:49.510 align:middle line:84%
And then out of
nowhere, I'm just

00:02:49.510 --> 00:02:52.510 align:middle line:84%
watching this scene
unfold in front of me.

00:02:52.510 --> 00:02:54.890 align:middle line:84%
And I'm watching a dead
body on the ground.

00:02:54.890 --> 00:02:57.260 align:middle line:90%
I'm watching a manager call 911.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:59.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm watching even
the customer asking

00:02:59.620 --> 00:03:01.490 align:middle line:84%
to have the manager
open the door.

00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:04.030 align:middle line:84%
And it's very
weird and odd to me

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:08.350 align:middle line:84%
because I can hear every
thought in anyone's head

00:03:08.350 --> 00:03:09.730 align:middle line:90%
that is near me.

00:03:09.730 --> 00:03:11.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm watching
everything from above,

00:03:11.590 --> 00:03:13.720 align:middle line:90%
which was also very odd to me.

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:17.170 align:middle line:84%
But it didn't dawn on me that
this dead body I was seeing

00:03:17.170 --> 00:03:20.270 align:middle line:84%
was me because the body
didn't look like me.

00:03:20.270 --> 00:03:23.660 align:middle line:84%
The neck had actually already
swollen wider than the jaw.

00:03:23.660 --> 00:03:27.910 align:middle line:84%
There was very, very pallid
purple and yellow tones

00:03:27.910 --> 00:03:28.910 align:middle line:90%
on the skin.

00:03:28.910 --> 00:03:32.290 align:middle line:84%
It didn't look-- it
almost didn't look human.

00:03:32.290 --> 00:03:35.770 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't think for a
second that that was me

00:03:35.770 --> 00:03:40.300 align:middle line:84%
because me was up here
watching what was going on.

00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:43.540 align:middle line:84%
I watched them bag this body
when the ambulance comes.

00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:44.870 align:middle line:90%
They pronounce it dead.

00:03:44.870 --> 00:03:46.000 align:middle line:90%
They put it in a body bag.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.520 align:middle line:84%
They put it on a
gurney and they put it

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.180 align:middle line:90%
in the back of the ambulance.

00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:52.270 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, the other
medics, there's

00:03:52.270 --> 00:03:53.870 align:middle line:90%
three medics that show up.

00:03:53.870 --> 00:03:55.580 align:middle line:84%
There's a rookie
who's brand new.

00:03:55.580 --> 00:03:57.920 align:middle line:84%
He's sitting in the
back with the body.

00:03:57.920 --> 00:04:01.130 align:middle line:10%
The other two are out
getting paperwork done.

00:04:01.130 --> 00:04:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And I could feel his
dismay because he felt

00:04:04.390 --> 00:04:06.860 align:middle line:90%
like I wanted to be a medic.

00:04:06.860 --> 00:04:09.110 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be an EMT
to make a difference.

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:11.240 align:middle line:84%
And he felt that he wasn't
making that difference.

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:15.010 align:middle line:84%
He felt that these veteran
medics didn't try for very long

00:04:15.010 --> 00:04:16.550 align:middle line:90%
to resuscitate the body.

00:04:16.550 --> 00:04:18.880 align:middle line:84%
He felt they should have
tried for 20 minutes, not just

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:20.019 align:middle line:90%
5 minutes.

00:04:20.019 --> 00:04:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And they're going
down the street.

00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:24.580 align:middle line:84%
As they pull away
from the scene,

00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:27.200 align:middle line:90%
I see this glow start to form.

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:30.150 align:middle line:84%
And it really looked like
a little miniature sun

00:04:30.150 --> 00:04:33.840 align:middle line:84%
starting to glow in the
heart space on the rookie

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:36.840 align:middle line:84%
medic who's sitting in
the back of the ambulance.

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:40.470 align:middle line:84%
I see it start to glow and
it got brighter and brighter.

00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:45.180 align:middle line:84%
And then I heard very
loudly, this one's not dead.

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:48.610 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know where that came
from, but I definitely heard it.

00:04:48.610 --> 00:04:52.140 align:middle line:84%
And I could tell that the
rookie medic heard it too.

00:04:52.140 --> 00:04:53.650 align:middle line:90%
Now, he froze.

00:04:53.650 --> 00:04:55.920 align:middle line:10%
He kind of froze as
soon as that was said,

00:04:55.920 --> 00:04:57.580 align:middle line:10%
but he didn't do
anything about it.

00:04:57.580 --> 00:04:59.910 align:middle line:84%
I could hear him
shrugging it off

00:04:59.910 --> 00:05:03.120 align:middle line:84%
as that must have just
been your imagination.

00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:06.180 align:middle line:84%
But they went another block down
the road and the light started

00:05:06.180 --> 00:05:07.770 align:middle line:90%
to glow even brighter.

00:05:07.770 --> 00:05:13.020 align:middle line:84%
And I heard for a second
time, this one's not dead.

00:05:13.020 --> 00:05:15.510 align:middle line:84%
And on that second
time, he responded.

00:05:15.510 --> 00:05:16.520 align:middle line:90%
He reacted.

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:18.160 align:middle line:90%
He unzipped the body bag.

00:05:18.160 --> 00:05:20.890 align:middle line:84%
He undid a couple of
straps around the body

00:05:20.890 --> 00:05:23.070 align:middle line:84%
so that he could reach
in and feel around

00:05:23.070 --> 00:05:24.630 align:middle line:90%
the neck area for a pulse.

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:27.190 align:middle line:84%
He didn't feel a pulse,
but it didn't stop him.

00:05:27.190 --> 00:05:28.050 align:middle line:90%
He kept going.

00:05:28.050 --> 00:05:30.540 align:middle line:84%
He was going to
attempt resuscitation.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.460 align:middle line:84%
So he forced oxygen
into the lungs.

00:05:33.460 --> 00:05:36.490 align:middle line:84%
He hooked up the body
to a defibrillator.

00:05:36.490 --> 00:05:38.820 align:middle line:84%
Well, the alarm is going
off and the other two medics

00:05:38.820 --> 00:05:40.890 align:middle line:84%
start just yelling
at him, saying,

00:05:40.890 --> 00:05:42.310 align:middle line:90%
you're going to get fired.

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:43.540 align:middle line:90%
You've got to stop this.

00:05:43.540 --> 00:05:44.830 align:middle line:90%
Stop what you're doing.

00:05:44.830 --> 00:05:46.390 align:middle line:90%
You're desecrating a dead body.

00:05:46.390 --> 00:05:47.530 align:middle line:90%
This is illegal.

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:48.790 align:middle line:90%
But he didn't care.

00:05:48.790 --> 00:05:51.270 align:middle line:84%
He went ahead and let
the first charge happen

00:05:51.270 --> 00:05:53.700 align:middle line:84%
and nothing happened
after the first charge.

00:05:53.700 --> 00:05:56.700 align:middle line:84%
He went ahead and let it
recharge for a second time

00:05:56.700 --> 00:05:58.960 align:middle line:84%
and they were still
chewing him out.

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:00.660 align:middle line:84%
But when the second
charge happened,

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:02.640 align:middle line:90%
there was one single heartbeat.

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:05.860 align:middle line:84%
It allowed the other two
medics to wait and watch.

00:06:05.860 --> 00:06:08.610 align:middle line:84%
They knew he was going
to go for a third round.

00:06:08.610 --> 00:06:12.310 align:middle line:84%
And right after, within
seconds of that third charge,

00:06:12.310 --> 00:06:14.830 align:middle line:84%
there was a steady
but faint heartbeat.

00:06:14.830 --> 00:06:18.490 align:middle line:84%
So the team began
resuscitation, procedures

00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:21.100 align:middle line:84%
of injecting things, and
doing all sorts of things

00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:22.190 align:middle line:90%
for the body.

00:06:22.190 --> 00:06:25.790 align:middle line:84%
But the body was having a really
hard time with coming back.

00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:28.840 align:middle line:84%
It was going into
seizures and they

00:06:28.840 --> 00:06:30.500 align:middle line:90%
were strapping the body down.

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:32.510 align:middle line:84%
I was watching the
strapping going on.

00:06:32.510 --> 00:06:35.170 align:middle line:84%
I didn't feel anything until
they got to the left arm.

00:06:35.170 --> 00:06:36.940 align:middle line:84%
But when they strapped
the left arm--

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:41.900 align:middle line:84%
I'm left handed-- I felt
them strapping my left arm.

00:06:41.900 --> 00:06:46.250 align:middle line:84%
And this was the first
inkling, the first idea

00:06:46.250 --> 00:06:48.800 align:middle line:84%
that what I'd been
watching this whole time

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:52.700 align:middle line:90%
was my very own death.

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:56.160 align:middle line:84%
>> I was working as a nurse
and I really loved my work.

00:06:56.160 --> 00:06:59.510 align:middle line:84%
I knew that was my calling when
I was a little girl, taking care

00:06:59.510 --> 00:07:01.610 align:middle line:84%
of other people,
especially people

00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:03.420 align:middle line:90%
who were very sick or dying.

00:07:03.420 --> 00:07:05.820 align:middle line:84%
And I worked in critical
care until I got hurt.

00:07:05.820 --> 00:07:08.640 align:middle line:84%
I got beat up by a patient
and that ended my career.

00:07:08.640 --> 00:07:12.320 align:middle line:84%
So I had to have spinal
surgery and have two disks

00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:15.990 align:middle line:84%
fused and hardware put in
to hold my spine together.

00:07:15.990 --> 00:07:18.390 align:middle line:84%
And I was at home
recovering from that.

00:07:18.390 --> 00:07:20.750 align:middle line:84%
I was hanging out with my
daughter, making smoothies,

00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:22.500 align:middle line:90%
and I started to feel odd.

00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:24.390 align:middle line:84%
My heart started
racing out of nowhere

00:07:24.390 --> 00:07:25.700 align:middle line:90%
and I'm not an anxious person.

00:07:25.700 --> 00:07:27.990 align:middle line:90%
And my mouth started itching.

00:07:27.990 --> 00:07:30.200 align:middle line:84%
I started having
trouble swallowing.

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wow,
I'm having some kind

00:07:33.170 --> 00:07:35.180 align:middle line:84%
of serious allergic
reaction and I could

00:07:35.180 --> 00:07:37.200 align:middle line:90%
tell it was moving quickly.

00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:39.420 align:middle line:84%
I was starting to itch
and break out in hives.

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:43.460 align:middle line:84%
And I had EpiPens on hand
for a shellfish allergy

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:45.750 align:middle line:84%
and I'd never, ever
had to use them.

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:47.490 align:middle line:90%
So I gave myself the injection.

00:07:47.490 --> 00:07:49.470 align:middle line:90%
My son drove me to the hospital.

00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:52.190 align:middle line:10%
I walked up to the
counter and the nurse that

00:07:52.190 --> 00:07:55.260 align:middle line:10%
was standing there just
was not the nurse you would

00:07:55.260 --> 00:07:58.360 align:middle line:10%
want to have if you were having
a life-threatening emergency.

00:07:58.360 --> 00:08:01.530 align:middle line:84%
So I was looking up because
I couldn't breathe very well

00:08:01.530 --> 00:08:04.000 align:middle line:84%
and anaphylaxis is
all I could say.

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, did
you take your EpiPen?

00:08:06.490 --> 00:08:07.690 align:middle line:90%
And I said, yes.

00:08:07.690 --> 00:08:09.720 align:middle line:84%
She said, well, if you
took your EpiPen, why did

00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:11.530 align:middle line:90%
you come to the emergency room?

00:08:11.530 --> 00:08:15.180 align:middle line:10%
And I thought, oh, man,
I'm going to die today.

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:18.010 align:middle line:10%
She said, we have a room, but
we don't have a bed in it.

00:08:18.010 --> 00:08:19.930 align:middle line:84%
And I can't put you in
a room without a bed.

00:08:19.930 --> 00:08:21.820 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I don't need a bed.

00:08:21.820 --> 00:08:22.810 align:middle line:90%
I need help.

00:08:22.810 --> 00:08:25.380 align:middle line:84%
So she put me in the
wheelchair and she wheeled me

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:27.730 align:middle line:84%
back down that hallway
and it's a dead end.

00:08:27.730 --> 00:08:30.510 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sitting back in this
hallway knowing no one can see

00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:33.059 align:middle line:84%
me and that I'm-- there's no
way I could get up and walk

00:08:33.059 --> 00:08:35.409 align:middle line:84%
because I'm having so
much trouble breathing.

00:08:35.409 --> 00:08:38.100 align:middle line:84%
And I was trying to get
someone's attention.

00:08:38.100 --> 00:08:39.370 align:middle line:90%
That wasn't working.

00:08:39.370 --> 00:08:41.700 align:middle line:84%
I had developed
stridor at that point,

00:08:41.700 --> 00:08:44.560 align:middle line:84%
which is a noise your throat
makes as it's swelling shut.

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:46.810 align:middle line:84%
So the stridor got
louder and louder.

00:08:46.810 --> 00:08:48.220 align:middle line:90%
And I saw this--

00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:49.810 align:middle line:84%
I think it was a
physician's assistant

00:08:49.810 --> 00:08:52.892 align:middle line:84%
stick her head around the corner
and she said, oh, my gosh.

00:08:52.892 --> 00:08:55.350 align:middle line:84%
And she came running down the
hall, grabbed the wheelchair,

00:08:55.350 --> 00:08:58.510 align:middle line:84%
ran down the hall with it, and
we get over to the trauma room.

00:08:58.510 --> 00:09:00.070 align:middle line:90%
My blood pressure was dropping.

00:09:00.070 --> 00:09:04.120 align:middle line:84%
So they started giving me
IV epinephrine, Benadryl.

00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:06.150 align:middle line:84%
My husband, my
fiancé at the time,

00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.250 align:middle line:84%
gets there and
walks into the room.

00:09:08.250 --> 00:09:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting in
the bed straight up,

00:09:09.930 --> 00:09:13.840 align:middle line:84%
looking straight up, and you
can just hear this whistling.

00:09:13.840 --> 00:09:16.590 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at the doctor and
said, if you don't do something,

00:09:16.590 --> 00:09:18.390 align:middle line:90%
she's going to stop breathing.

00:09:18.390 --> 00:09:20.820 align:middle line:84%
And he said, no, no, no,
we've got plenty of time

00:09:20.820 --> 00:09:22.000 align:middle line:90%
before that happens.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:25.500 align:middle line:84%
And by my husband's telling,
it's less than five minutes

00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:27.660 align:middle line:90%
and I just collapse.

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:32.610 align:middle line:84%
But I immediately popped out of
my body and was over the top,

00:09:32.610 --> 00:09:34.150 align:middle line:90%
in the corner watching.

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:35.790 align:middle line:90%
And I heard the code call.

00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:37.935 align:middle line:84%
I thought, uh-oh,
somebody's in trouble.

00:09:37.935 --> 00:09:39.810 align:middle line:84%
And then everybody came
running into the room

00:09:39.810 --> 00:09:41.950 align:middle line:84%
and I thought, oh, it's
that lady in the bed.

00:09:41.950 --> 00:09:43.330 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know who she was.

00:09:43.330 --> 00:09:47.260 align:middle line:84%
So they all came in and
started to work on me.

00:09:47.260 --> 00:09:48.240 align:middle line:90%
They code me.

00:09:48.240 --> 00:09:50.940 align:middle line:84%
I hear the tongue blade
snap and I go out.

00:09:50.940 --> 00:09:54.120 align:middle line:84%
And the next time I wake
up, I'm in my sister's car.

00:09:54.120 --> 00:09:55.590 align:middle line:90%
She's driving down the road.

00:09:55.590 --> 00:09:58.460 align:middle line:84%
She's coming from
Wisconsin to Kentucky

00:09:58.460 --> 00:10:00.360 align:middle line:90%
to be with me and the kids.

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:01.740 align:middle line:90%
And it's pouring rain.

